<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/571b.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                    <gloss type="to">Brown Brothers and Company</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Kindly telegraph the amount now owed you by Nicaragua, and send by mail
                            the terms and conditions on which you would increase your <pb facs="1151" n="1047" xml:id="pg_1047"/> loan for about one year to
                            between $2,000,000 and $2,500,000; also state whether you would consider
                            your security on the latter amount ample without option on the
                            railroad.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>